</div>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Sophisticated, romantic, precious. Blush in all its forms is continuing its reign into 2018. The near opposite of the bold hued trend, blush offers a calmer color palette. Beautifully reimagining our homes, the various shades of pale pink have been slowly growing in popularity over the years. From Pantone's Rose Quartz to last years Millennial Pink, the trend of comforting pink is emerging as a top design concept. Working in unison with bolder shades or simply as the statement color, blush creates harmony in any space.  </p>
