<p><strong>MIXED METALLICS</strong></p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center"><a href="https://www.houzz.com/photo/46745466-transitional-living-room-transitional-living-room-denver" target="_blank"><img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/images/Trends-2018Predictions-MixedMetals1.jpg"></a></div>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Once considered an absolute 'no-no', mixing metallics is now one of this years most popular trends. Adding visual interest in the places least expected is attracting many to this idea. No longer considered dramatic, metallics have become the new neutrals for 2018. From hardware, to walls, to textiles, metallic sheens are being found throughout the home. Their surprising ability to work in unity with their surroundings has brought them to the forefront of design. Eye-catching yet sleek, metallics make a statement without overwhelming. </p>
